<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY COMMITTEE</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="color:#232323; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Association of Chief Police Officers (ACPO) (FSS038)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Does the Government have an effective strategy for forensic science in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> and is it sufficient to support forensic science R&amp;D and criminal justice?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Tra</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ditionally the Police Service a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">nd the CJS struggled to define its fundamental requirements from forensic science, with services largely being provider driven and change delivered piecemeal. ACPO recognised this and in conjunction with the Association of Police Authorities and the Home Office commissioned a piece of work in 2006 which became the Forensics21 Programme. The programme had strong governance through the ACPO Forensic Portfolio and until recently was delivered by the NPIA.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Forensics21 was designed to create a coherent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> set of forensic services, capabilities and skills within the Police Service and externally, which deliver continuous improvements in policing outcomes, to assured quality standards, and provide demonstrable and increasing value for money.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO leadership allowed the work to be split into business areas supporting:</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Performance &amp; Quality Standards</span></h1><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Marketplace Strategy (Procurement)</span></h1><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Science and Innovation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">; this business area seeks to focus innovation on operational </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">need </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">(please refer to point 3.3)</span></h1><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Information Services</span></h1><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">upplemented by The DNA Strategy Board which was more recently placed on a statutory footing.</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Whilst these business areas are responsible for the governance of individual projects, the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Forensic Portfolio </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">was able to ensure that delivery was joined up and utilised force expert networks</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">structure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">has proved very</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> effective </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">to date and has seen </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">successful </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">delivery in a number of areas including transition of the National DNA Database into the Home Office (was NPIA), delivery of 2 forensic procurement frameworks, establishing a quality culture within police forensics and a number of process improvements across the whole forensic operating model.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">With the recent closure of the NPIA the Forensics21 team have migrated across several Home Office Departments including CAST and HO Commercial; it remains to be seen if the same level of successful change can continue.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Did the FSS transition and closure run smoothly and within budget?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">At the point of the announcement,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> on 14</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> December 2010,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> the FSS was still the predominant Supplier to the police forces and the vast majority of forensic laboratory services were being delivered to forces under either the National Forensic Framework Agreement (NFFA) or the West Coast Consortium (WCC) Contract, together involving twelve Forensic Suppliers all, with the exception of the FSS, were fully in the private sector. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">It is also worthy of highlighting for contextual purposes that the FSS closure and transition also coincided with the closure and wind-down of the NPIA, from where most of the staff involved in the FSS transition activities, worked.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">From the police service perspective, the transition of work away from the FSS was executed under four main pillars of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">activity:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Operation Slingshot (involving formal re-tendering of FSS services and extending local SLAs were possible)</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Contract Novation to alternative Suppliers where multiple suppliers were already under contract (WCC for 14 forces</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">, (3 police regions – NW/SW/Wales)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">)</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">NE region pursuing the Accelerated Mergers &amp; Acquisition (AMA) solution with the FSS and PwC</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">MPS introduction of a new operating model and take-over of the FSS Lambeth Laboratory</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">All four pillars were brought together, managed and coordinated through the Forensic Transition Board (FTB), Chaired by the Minister James Brokenshire</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> which met regularly throughout the FSS wind-down period.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> Whilst each of the four pillars themselves were very complex, the process was considered to be effective and reduced the risk of failure; each </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">delivered their respective solutions in time for the closure.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt"><tr style="height:22.25pt"><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:86.4pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Pillar</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:225pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Milestone</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:131.7pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Date</span></p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="6" style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom