-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:225pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Services transitioned away from FSS to new suppliers</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:131.7pt"><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">By end 2011</span></p></td></tr></table><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Throughout all this unprecedented activity and major fundamental change in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">delivery models</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">, there has been no actual failure of supply at any point in the process. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Operation Slingshot and the Contract Novations were led by ACPO and the Slingshot/WCC teams. Each and every deliverable and milestone was met and all services were transition</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> in time for FSS closure. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">his aspect ran smoothly.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Throughout the process very close attention was paid at a national level for the monitoring of laboratory submissions. The overriding primary objective was continuity of forensic supply for the police service. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">For the NE and MPS solutions, these were led separately by their respective chief officer teams.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">A major</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> element of complexity in the transition programme wa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">s the long period of time taken to decide upon the constituents of any AMA solution and whether the NE region would in fact opt for that process. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">In order to mitigate the potential for the AMA failing, resulting in discontinuity of forensic services to the NE, their requirements were included within Slingshot planning. This, however, led to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> a great deal of uncertainty and lack of clarity given to the potential bidders for the re-tendering work.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">On reflection, it would have been much better if any AMA solutions were delivered first, then to undertake re-tendering activities for whatever services were left, rather than do the two in parallel. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">2.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The complexity of forensic services involved in the FSS closure &amp; transition is such that it is difficult to state exactly what savings, if any, forces are achieving as a result. It must be stated again though, that the overriding primary objective was one of continuity of services, and achieving savings was an added bonus, if it happened at all.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What impacts have the FSS’s closure had on (i) the criminal justice system and (ii) forensic science R&amp;D and training? In particular, have the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">appropriate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> quality standards and accreditation been rigorously maintained?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> for some time</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> stated their commitment to the delivery of accredited quality standards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> across forensic services; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">delivered internally and externally by forensic providers. ACPO also fully supports the work of the Forensic Science Regulator and the development of his Codes of Practice.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">For example, t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">he N</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ational </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">orensic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ramework – </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">N</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ext </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">eneration</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> (NFFNG)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> requires that Suppliers meet the appropriate Quality Standards &amp; Accreditation requirements, as set by the Forensic Regulator (principally ISO17025), together with a requirement to undertake research &amp; development with a view to improving efficiency &amp; effectiveness and making use of the latest available technological advances.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> Each Suppliers accreditation status is re-assessed by the F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">orensic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">arketplace </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">anagement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">eam (FMMT)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> at every regional mini-competition to ensure standards are maintained and built upon. In addition to this and as a normal business as usual function, quality incidents are also routinely monitored, reported and where appropriate, referred to the Forensic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> Science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> Regulator.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">In addition, the Science and Innovation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Board within</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> the Forensic Portfolio is working hard to engage with academia, industry and the commercial sector to encourage R&amp;D </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">and has recently published an open source document to provide providers of research and development an insight into the problems faced by the police service; ‘Harnessing Science and Innovation for Forensic Investigation in Policing’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">. Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> Science and Innovation Board is also currently working with several providers who are developing rapid DNA technology, under the Forensics21 ADAPT project (Accelerated DNA Profiling Technology). Although the FSS were one potential provider of ADAPT technology, there are several others in the marketplace.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO have never relied upon the FSS to deliver training and therefore its closure has not had an impact on the delivery of forensic training within forces; current needs are largely fulfilled through the newly created </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">College</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Policing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What should be the role of the Forensic Science Regulator?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">fully </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">support</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> the Forensic Science Regulator in his role and believe he should be the gatekeeper for setting the appropriate standards for implementation across police forensics. The office of the FSR should be available to provide advice and guidance to forces in their work to achieve the standards and keep a central repository of feedback, lessons learned and information in relat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ion to known quality failures.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The FSR should not be seen as the regulator of the forensic science marketplace </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">itself </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">or the providers of forensic science within it.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> size of the forensics market and how stable is it?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Based on the ‘projected’, regional mini-competition demand for services, the estimated value of the forensic market for services under the NFFNG is approximately somewhere between £80 - £90m pa.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Research conducted on ‘actual’ spend data would suggest that the real market value position is somewhat lower at somewhere around £65 - £80m pa.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">It is likely we will see further reductions in the size of the market value due </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">to:</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Reducing police force budgets manifesting itself in reduced laboratory submissions</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">More intellig</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ent laboratory submissions focu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">sing better on the needs of the case being investigated.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Streamlined Forensic Reporting (SFR) which results in only those matters being ‘disputed’ by the defence, being subject to extended forensic analysis.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Forces pursuing different</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">, and more efficient, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">operating models</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">, developing their own quality accredited laboratory facilities.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The combined effect of the forthcoming procurement activity, the continued FSS transition and legacy issues and potentially a shrinking market value, will mean we will continue to see an unstable forensic supply market for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">next 6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">18 months</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Longer turnaround times (TRT) may be seen as a result which has the potential to impact the CJS and on the timeliness of cases, especially those with a high content of scientific evidence and/or those of a complex nature. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Despite there being no actual failure of supply at any point so far, not unsurprisingly, we are experiencing very challenging times with the Suppliers as the new services, procurement activity and force operating models become established.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">To mitigate the risks associated with this, a vast array of activities are undertaken by the FMMT and Forces to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">monitor supplier performance, capacity, q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">uality</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">tandards and market dynamics. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The FMMT liaises closely with all forces, suppliers and other agencies such as the Forensic Regulator, CPS and the United Kingdom Accreditation Service (UKAS) to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ensure continuity of supply </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> complies with the appropriate q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">uality standards. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">In addition to this the FMMT, on behal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">f of the forces, re-assess all s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">uppliers at each regional mini-com</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">petition, against criteria for accreditation, s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ecurity and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">business c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ontinuity &amp; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">isaster </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ecovery planning.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Overarching governance of the marketplace is provided in two ways;</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">he Home Office Forensic Policy Group</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">chaired</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> by Stephen Webb and will support the effective provision of forensic science services to the Criminal Justice System</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">. It is concerned with ensuring that there is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> a vibrant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">, agile,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> competitive and resilient market which drives cost effective approaches, and innovation. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The Forensic Marketplace Strategy Group is chaired by CC Chris Eyre (ACPO Lead) and provides strategic oversight &amp; direction on the forensic marketplace development. This includes ensuring the effective and efficient operation of the forensic procurement framework and compliance with the Mini-Competition Pipeline. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">A summary of current marketplace issues and an assessment of their impact and likely timelines are as follows.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">5.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Since the closure of the FSS there has been a:</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">National</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> shortage of appropriately experienced/qualified scientific staff for reporting casework toxicology results. This is leading to longer turnaround times (TRTs) for cases with such submissions with typical TRTs currently</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> upwards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> of 5-6 weeks as opposed to 3 weeks. </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The impact of this issue has been described by forces as ‘manageable’ but requiring significant resources to manage timelines and critical CJS dates. The suppliers providing this service have attempted to recruit additional staff but are also undertaking significant internal training programmes to develop their own new staff for this area of specialism. Expected complete resolution date 31.3.13.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">There are national capacity issues with Drugs analysis service suppliers, resulting in longer than expected turnaround times and this has led to a significant backlog at some suppliers. Current TRTs are in the region of 7-8 weeks rather than 3. The impact of this issue is, again, on timeliness of delivery of reports to the CJS and requires significant management by force staff to avoid detrimental effect on cases. This is being monitored very closely and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">alternative sources of supply for this service are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> being sourced. Expected complete resolution date 31.12.12.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How are forensic science </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> procured by police forces and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">could</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> processes be improved?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The current NFFA expired on 31</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> July 2012 and its’ replacement, the National Forensic Framework – Next Generation (NFFNG) was established on 1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> August 2012, by way of full EU OJEU tender exercise led by the NPIA &amp; Home Office.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The Home Office </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> the contracting authority for the NFFNG and it is the intention that all forces (and other law enforcement agencies) will use this framework to procure their forensic laboratory services in future. The NFFNG expires on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">31</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> July 2016</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The NFFNG includes laboratory services across 13 Packages or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Lots:</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">DNA PACE</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">DNA Crime Stain</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">DNA Other</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Fire Investigation</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Footwear</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Firearms</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Drugs</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Noxious Substances</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Question Documents</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Case Review</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Toxicology</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">General Casework</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Trace Evidence</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The number of Suppliers for each </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Lot</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> varies and is between two (for DNA PACE) and 6 (for Toxicology &amp; Case Review), thus presenting the forces with a range of Suppliers to choose from whilst also maintaining healthy competition in the market.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">As part of the tender process, 19 Suppliers originally expressed an interest in bidding for a place on the new framework and following the pre-Qualification phase and the ITT evaluation process itself, 13 Suppliers were successful and were awarded a place on the framework. This included three brand new entrants into the market and at least five S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ubject </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">atter </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">xperts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> in total.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The current Suppliers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">are:</span></h2><h3 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="fon