id; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Mass Spec Analytical</span></h3><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Police forces wishing to procure services under the NFFNG will run short, regional mini-competitions to select their preferred Supplier(s) from those on the framework. They will then award local service contracts with those Suppliers.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">In order to prevent swamping the market with multiple procurement activit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> at any given </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">time,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> there is a need to manage the future police force procurements and as such a Pipeline for regional tenders under the NFFNG over the next 4 years has been agreed with forces and circulated to the Suppliers.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The Pipeline, Supplier relationships, the NFFNG terms &amp; conditions and aspects such as performance, quality, accreditation etc, together with general marketplace dynamics are being monitored</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">by a central Home Office team (Forensic Marketplace Management team – FMMT). </span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">To date, the pipeline activities remain on target and as per schedule, with the WCC having completed their regional mini-competition and the South-East region having started theirs as planned.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">As with any ‘national’ initiative, the current forensic framework attempts to cater for the needs of the whole range of forces, from large to small and a such may not represent the ideal solution for every single individual fo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">rce. It does however provide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> the majority of forces w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ith the tools</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> they need to procure these services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> including standardised contractual Terms &amp; Conditions and nationally agreed User Specifications.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Inevitably though, compromises have been made in the development and ‘one size may not fit all’.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The NFFNG is not a mandated national framework and as such forces are at liberty to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">rocure in another way, although it is strongly anticipated that most forces will use it.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">6.13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Examples where alternatives are currently being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">utilised:</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The North-East region are tendering separately for a longer term, ‘managed service’ type contract which will need to be in place by April 2013. Bids from Suppliers have been submitted and are currently being evaluated.</span></h2><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The MPS have a different operating model based on only out-sourcing the ‘analytical services’ and undertaking all other work themselves.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Has the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">closure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> of the FSS resulted in a loss of intellectual wealth through its scientists leaving the forensic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> profession, or the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO does not have a detailed insight into this issue although, in general, forces have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">experienced</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> continuity in supply of quality forensic services. ACPO also recognises that police forensics represents a very small proportion of the whole of the forensic landscape</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">, e.g.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> medical forensics, forensic psychiatry,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> forensic engineering etc. and therefore there continues to be a vast wealth of experience and expertise still in existence in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">.</span></h2><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Are current arrangements for the FSS’s archives satisfactory? How could arrangements for the retention of case files and forensic materials in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> be improved?</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">8.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">The current arrangements for the archives are working satisfactorily and forces are able to readily access their case files and materials utilising the processes put in place. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Experience to date would suggest there are two potential areas for improvement:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">:</span></h2><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Currently requests for files and materials can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be submitted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> from many </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">departments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and personnel within a force and therefore any given force does not necessarily have a full picture of what has been retrieved. This could be improved by having a national protocol whereby a single signatory/ group of signatories are registered to main</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> an overview and control within each force.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Some requests for materials require an understanding of what </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">constitutes a case file and in what form</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> various retained materials can take. In the absence of any organisational and scientific knowledge within the archive forces are attempting to make these decisions themselves. This could be improved if the archives had access to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or employed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ex-FSS scientists to assist in this process.</span></li></ul><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Declaration of Interest</span></h1><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">9.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">ACPO was the main customer of the FSS throughout its existence. Once the decision was made to close the FSS ACPO led the Operation Slingshot element of the transition programme to ensure a continuity of supply within the forensic market and chaired the project board to safeguard the FSS archive.</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2013</span></p></div></body></html>